Step 1: Convert your summary stats to BED format

BED format is 0-based, half-open. So we subtract 1 from the POS column for start.

tail -n +2 summary_stats.txt | awk 'BEGIN{OFS="\t"} {print "chr"$2, $3-1, $3, $1}' > input.bed


This takes lines after the header (tail -n +2)

Outputs: chr, start, end, rsID

CrossMap bed hg19ToHg38.over.chain.gz input_crossmap.bed output_crossmap.bed

The output_crossmap.bed will look like:

chr1	210030	210031	rs1404691466

python3 lifted.py
